# Cursor Rules for Honoo Project

## Language Settings
- All communication, documentation, and AI-generated content must be in Japanese (日本語)
- Pull request descriptions, commit messages, and code comments should be written in Japanese
- When generating PR descriptions, use clear and professional Japanese
- Code comments should be in Japanese unless the codebase convention requires otherwise

## PR Description Guidelines
- PRのタイトルと説明は日本語で記述する
- 変更内容を明確に説明する
- 技術的な詳細も日本語で説明する
- 関連するIssueやタスクへの言及も日本語で行う

## Commit Message Guidelines
- コミットメッセージは日本語で記述する
- 変更の目的と内容を簡潔に説明する

## Code Style
- Follow the existing codebase patterns and conventions
- Maintain consistency with Vue 3 Composition API patterns used in this project
- Use TypeScript for type safety

## Workflow and Thinking Process
- Always use Serena tools for code analysis, symbol search, and codebase exploration
- Before making changes, use Serena's semantic search and symbol tools to understand the codebase structure
- Use Serena's symbolic tools (find_symbol, get_symbols_overview, etc.) instead of reading entire files when possible
- Leverage Serena's intelligent code reading capabilities to work efficiently and avoid unnecessary file reads
- When exploring code, start with high-level overviews using Serena tools before diving into specific implementations

